spec-testspec-subpage: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for spec-style tests.
spec-testspec-invoke: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for spec-style tests.
spec-testcase-subpage: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for testcase-style tests.
spec-testcase-invoke: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for testcase-style tests.
spec-default-subpage: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-subpage-desc}} Used while creating a link to the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for default tests, that is the catch all.
spec-default-invoke: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-invoke-desc}} Used while invoking the module on the subpage holding the test code. This is the version used for default tests, that is the catch all.
spec-test-text-good: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests were ok.
spec-test-text-pending: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|pending}} A pending result is one where one or more reported tests were pending.
spec-test-text-fail: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests were not ok.
spec-test-text-missing: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|missing}} A missing result is one where the test page could not be found.
spec-test-text-unknown: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|unknown}} An unknown result is one where the reported tests could not be parsed.
spec-test-text-todo-good: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests marked "todo" were ok.
spec-test-text-todo-fail: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests marked "todo" were not ok.
spec-test-text-skip-good: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|good}} A good result is one where all reported tests marked "skip" were ok.
spec-test-text-skip-fail: {{spec-gloss}} {{spec-indicator-desc|failed}} A failed result is one where one or more reported tests marked "skip" were not ok.
spec-track-log-header: {{spec-gloss}} Description used on top of Special:log when filtered on this specific log.
spec-track-log-entry-good: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be good according to the TAP-format.
spec-track-log-entry-pending: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be pending.
spec-track-log-entry-fail: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result is found to be failing according to the TAP-format.
spec-track-log-entry-exists: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, but the result is something else than a valid TAP-format.
spec-track-log-entry-missing: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage does not exists.
spec-track-log-entry-unknown: {{spec-gloss}} {{logentry}} This is used when the subpage exists, and the result can't be established in any known way.
spec-console-title: {{spec-gloss}} Area used for test reports. Can be empty, but will then have a message about this.
spec-console-empty: {{spec-gloss}} Message used to clarify that the output area is initially empty.
spec-console-cleared: {{spec-gloss}} Message used to clarify that the output area is cleared.
spec-console-run: {{spec-gloss}} Button to initiate a run of a test case. After the completed run the report will be appended to the output area.
spec-console-clear: {{spec-gloss}} Button to initiate a clearing of previous test cases. After clearing the output area a message to the effect will be injected.
spec-report-skip-no-message: {{spec-gloss}} [delete entry?] Error message for non-existing message keys. Indicates a missing or wrong implementation, possibly on some kind of extension.
spec-frame-compact-header-all-good: {{spec-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the compact layout when all contained constituents are good. Initial "ok" must be retained, but can be followed by an explanation.
spec-frame-compact-header-some-failed: {{spec-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the compact layout when some contained constituents have failed. Initial "not ok" must be retained, but can be followed by an explanation.
spec-frame-full-header: {{spec-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the full layout. Initial hash (#) must be retained.
spec-frame-vivid-header: {{spec-gloss}} [delete entry?]] Header message used for the full layout.
spec-report-result-compact-is-ok: {{spec-gloss}} Initial keyword "ok" used for each good test in a TAP-report. It can be adapted by a following localization "ok (something)", but keep the "ok". {{spec-report-compact}}}
spec-report-result-compact-is-not-ok: {{spec-gloss}} Initial keyword "not ok" used for each good test in a TAP-report. It can be adapted by a following localization "not ok (something)", but keep the "not ok". {{spec-report-compact}}}
spec-report-result-compact-wrap-skip: {{spec-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "skip" keyword and the optional string. It can be adapted by a following localization "skip (something)". {{spec-report-compact}}}
spec-report-result-compact-wrap-todo: {{spec-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the "todo" keyword and the optional string. It can be freely adapted, but should not contain a hash mark. {{spec-report-compact}}}
spec-report-result-compact-wrap-descript: {{spec-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the description optional string. {{spec-report-compact}}}
spec-report-result-compact-wrap-line: {{spec-gloss}} An outher wrapper for the collected lines. {{spec-report-compact}}}
